  "response": "Here are several ways to find a good book editor:\n\n1. Professional Editing Associations\n- Editorial Freelancers Association (EFA)\n- American Copy Editors Society (ACES)\n- Professional Editors Network\n\n2. Online Platforms\n- Reedsy\n- Upwork\n- Freelancer\n- Fiverr\n\n3. Personal Recommendations\n- Writers' groups\n- Writing conferences\n- Author forums\n- Social media writing communities\n\n4. Publishing Industry Connections\n- Literary agents\n- Publishing consultants\n- Writing workshops\n\n5. Academic Sources\n- University writing departments\n- Graduate writing programs\n\n6. Specialized Editing Websites\n- ProEdit\n- EditProse\n- Scribendi\n\n7. Genre-Specific Resources\n- Look for editors specializing in your book's genre\n\nTips for selecting an editor:\n- Review their portfolio\n- Check references\n- Request sample edits\n- Discuss rates and timelines\n- Ensure they understand your vision\n- Verify their experience in your genre\n\nConsider your budget and specific editing needs (developmental, line, copy editing) when choosing.",
